title: FIFA U-17 World Cup 2015: Australia 1-4 Germany
text:
Captain Felix Passlack, who scored three times as Germany finished runners-up at the 2015 UEFA U-17 Championship in Bulgaria back in May, opened the scoring in the 14th minute before a double from Johannes Eggestein (25th, 39th) had Australia trailing 3-0 at the half-time interval.
Pierce Waring pulled one back for Australia with a sublime chip ten minutes into the second half only for Germany - semi-finalists at two of the last four FIFA U-17 World Cups - to restore their three-goal lead through a stunning 65th minute shot from the edge of the area from Vitaly Janlet, who was a late call up to Christian Wuck’s squad following an injury to Niklas Dorsch.
“We kept the ball possession and were intense in some moments, but couldn’t create chances to score and it’s disappointing,” reflected Australia coach Tony Vidmar.
“They are very clinical and defended much better. It was the first match and in other tournaments there were teams that lost 6-1 and qualified, so what we have to do is take the positive aspects and move forward to the next match.”
Australia will be looking to pick up their first win on Wednesday when they face back-to-back FIFA U-17 World Cup finalists Mexico before rounding off their Group C matches three days later against Argentina.
